Nov 8 2009 	Try this one for location and comfort	After pricing lodging elsewhere we decided to give the Lombard area a try and were glad that we did. Our room was large and comfortable. There was some noise from the hallway, but it was due to inconsiderate guests and not the fault of the hotel. The location is excellent - close enough to the sights of the city but not in the middle of the rush. Parking was free and monitored by security cameras in the lobby. Restaurants were nearby. We had a guidebook indicating prices and were given a &quot;Manager's Special&quot; that dropped it even further, to just over $100 plus tax for a night in San Francisco. This is one of four associated properties on Lombard, and we would have been comfortable with any of them.The little breakfast spot adjoining the elevator was good. Try Mel's Diner across the street for terrific burgers and milkshakes.	
